caption.body: Airlines have been known to go all out with the designs of their liveries, whether produced in collaboration with famous designers, celebrating partner brands, or showcasing destinations. One iconic collaboration is between beloved Japanese brand Sanrio and EVA Air. Sanrio's most popular character, Hello Kitty, a cartoon cat (although Sanrio does not refer to her as a cat), decorated multiple Airbus 330s and serviced routes from Taipei, Taiwan, to various international destinations. These aircraft feature many themed amenities such as this Hello Kitty printed roll of toilet paper.   roll of toilet paper: EVA Air, Hello Kitty; 2014 Gift of Vincent Ma 2021.020.0359  https://bit.ly/3vRUox2
